Fall sports practices will begin on Monday, August 17th. More information on practice times and locations will come soon.

All 7th-12th grade students planning to participate in a fall sport in 2020 must complete a sports physical as well as complete the rSchool documents. This must be done before they are allowed to practice. Be sure all questions are answered on the physical and all signature lines are complete. Use the link for instructions on completing the required rSchool consent forms.

post_text: We would like to welcome Wayne Carter as our newest member to the Apple Bus family. He has been hired as the General Manager of transportation for the Atchison 409 School District. Wayne was raised in Kansas where he lived most of his life. He and his wife moved away for two years and are very glad to be back home. Wayne brings multiple years of management experience, safety and security experience, DOT compliance experience and working with school districts as a track and football coach for 27 years. He has had a lot of experience working with students. He currently holds a Class A CDL, and is CPR and CPI certified. His wife is the Special Needs Director of Doniphan County and they have four grown boys. We look forward to a long working relationship with Wayne and are glad to have him join our team. Welcome Wayne! #WeAre409

post_text:
Help us welcome Andrea Coppinger to the USD 409 Family! Andrea will be the AES Primary Associate Principal. She comes to us with 14 years of teaching experience in grades 2, 5, and most recently middle school math at Fort Leavenworth and Pleasant Ridge respectively.

Andrea received a Master of Arts in School Leadership and a B.A. in Elementary Education from Benedctine and a Master of Arts in Education from Baker University. Throughout Andrea’s career she has served on numerous leadership committees, including both the Building and District leadership teams as well as the Instructional Support Team. Andrea shared, “I am incredibly honored to begin my leadership career at Atchison Elementary School. I am a passionate educator dedicated to building strong relationships with students, staff, families and community members.” #notyouraverageaviator #WeAre409

post_text:
Please help us welcome Dakota Matthew, our new high school and middle school choir director to the 409 Family!

Dakota Mathew is a recent graduate from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln and the new choir director! In college he was involved in the collegiate show choir, Big Red Singers, University Singers, New Student Enrollment, and the Cornhusker Marching Band! He enjoys music by Ben Rector, Chipotle, Star Wars, and spending time with friends at the lake. When he’s not working on music related things, he likes to spend his time on the golf course.

He is excited to join the Atchison music team and is looking forward to continuing the rising success of the program! He can’t wait to meet the students and staff at AHS and create unique, meaningful connections with each of them! #WeAre409

City of Atchison, Kansas Local Government
April 30 at 3:30 PM ·

With news from the Kansas Governor's Office planning to be released this evening about reopening Kansas, we want to address the many questions you may have about what this means for our local community.

We will be hosting another Live Community COVID-19 Q&A next Monday, May 4th, at 6:00pm on the City’s Facebook page.
Atchison City Manager Becky Berger, Atchison Public Schools Superintendent Renee Scott, Director of Atchison County KS Emergency Management Wes Lanter, Atchison County Health Department Officer Lori Forge, and Atchison Hospital Chief Medical Officer Dr. Norma Green will be live to answer questions from the public. Representative John Eplee will also be live to relate information about the state legislature’s response to COVID-19.

Questions? You can submit them ahead of time here: https://survey.zohopublic.com/zs/GxBUkt.

City of Atchison, Kansas Local Government
April 30 at 3:30 PM ·

With news from the Kansas Governor's Office planning to be released this evening about reopening Kansas, we want to address the many questions you may have about what this means for our local community.

We will be hosting another Live Community COVID-19 Q&A next Monday, May 4th, at 6:00pm on the City’s Facebook page.
Atchison City Manager Becky Berger, Atchison Public Schools Superintendent Renee Scott, Director of Atchison County KS Emergency Management Wes Lanter, Atchison County Health Department Officer Lori Forge, and Atchison Hospital Chief Medical Officer Dr. Norma Green will be live to answer questions from the public. Representative John Eplee will also be live to relate information about the state legislature’s response to COVID-19.

Questions? You can submit them ahead of time here: https://survey.zohopublic.com/zs/GxBUkt.

post_text: We are delighted to welcome Patrick Battle to Atchison as our new history teacher at Central School and the new Head Boys Basketball Coach at AHS. Patrick is a passionate educator who cares deeply about helping his students find success in the classroom and on the court. He has 30 years of high school basketball coaching experience and 20 years of teaching experience. He has a bachelor's degree from the University of Colorado at Colorado Springs and Kansas State University as well as a Masters Degree from Concordia University, California. Throughout his coaching career, he has been the Head Varsity Boys Coach at Junction City High School for five years and at Pleasant Ridge High School for a total of 10 years over two separate stints. He has accumulated 170 career varsity victories and has been a part of a Colorado State Championship and a 6A Kansas State Runner-Up Team. We are lucky to have him become a part of our district as he shares our desire to build a program that will make our community proud. Welcome to the USD 409 Family Patrick! #WeAre409

Sorry, we forgot to give you times for food pick-up starting tomorrow! Pick-Up times are from 11:00 am-1:00 pm.

Beginning Tuesday, March 17, 2020, a non-congregate school meals program will be available to any person age 1 to 18 years of age.

Students must pick up the meals from a designated location. This will be accomplished in a “drive-through” fashion. One lunch and one breakfast will be provided per visible student. Children must be present for meals to be received.
Locations:

Atchison Elementary School back parking lot
Atchison Middle School teacher parking lot (6th & Santa Fe)
First Assembly of God Church parking lot (1004 S. 5th)
St. Benedict School parking lot ( 201 Division Street - southeast parking lot off of 2nd street).

When picking up meals you will be notified of which items are perishable at room temperature. These items will need to be consumed, refrigerated, or thrown away within one hour of pickup for safety purposes.

Kansas Counts
March 10 at 1:42 PM ·

2020 Census Invitations Start Arriving This Week!

95% or about 143 million households in the country will receive an initial invitation to respond to the 2020 Census in their mailboxes between March 12 and 20. Households are encouraged to respond when they receive their invitation.

Learn more at http://KansasCounts.org

#KansasCounts #2020Census

We are still looking for family members of elementary students and middle school students to take our Parent/Guardian Survey. AES needs around 200 family members to take the survey and the middle school needs around 80. We need about 150 more to take the survey. It should take about 15 minutes and you are welcome to take it tonight at conferences! We will also have a booth set up at the high school home game Friday. If you fill it out at the game you can grab a bag of free popcorn! We use this feedback to help us make decisions for your children and to help us make USD 409 the best place for your children to go to school. If you have any questions about the survey please do not hesitate to call your child's school principals! #weare409
